1
00:00:18,458 --> 00:00:20,708
- Narrator: IN A LAND
FAR, FAR AWAY

2
00:00:20,791 --> 00:00:23,041
LIES THE KINGDOM
OF FIORE.

3
00:00:23,125 --> 00:00:26,208
A SMALL, PEACEFUL NATION
OF 17 MILLION,

4
00:00:26,291 --> 00:00:28,791
AND A PLACE FILLED
WITH MAGIC.

5
00:00:28,875 --> 00:00:30,291
FOUND IN EVERY HOME,

6
00:00:30,375 --> 00:00:32,041
BOUGHT AND SOLD
IN EVERY MARKETPLACE.

7
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:34,375
FOR MOST MAGIC IS
MERELY A TOOL,

8
00:00:34,458 --> 00:00:36,958
A MUNDANE PART
OF EVERYDAY LIFE.

9
00:00:37,041 --> 00:00:39,333
FOR SOME, HOWEVER,
MAGIC IS AN ART,

10
00:00:39,416 --> 00:00:42,416
AND THEY'VE DEVOTED
THEIR LIVES TO ITS PRACTICE.

11
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,666
THESE ARE THE WIZARDS.

12
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:46,833
BANDED TOGETHER INTO
MAGICAL GUILDS,

13
00:00:46,916 --> 00:00:50,416
THEY PLY THEIR SKILLS
IN SEARCH OF FAME AND FORTUNE.

14
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:54,375
MANY SUCH GUILDS DOT
THE LANDSCAPE OF FIORE.

15
00:00:54,458 --> 00:00:57,416
BUT THERE IS A CERTAIN GUILD
IN A CERTAIN TOWN

16
00:00:57,500 --> 00:00:59,750
THAT SOARS HIGH
ABOVE THE REST.

17
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:02,583
ONE FROM WHICH COUNTLESS LEGENDS
HAVE BEEN BORN.

18
00:01:02,666 --> 00:01:05,750
A GUILD THAT WOULD NO DOUBT
CONTINUE TO CREATE LEGENDS

19
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:07,416
WELL INTO THE FUTURE.

20
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:11,500
ITS NAME IS FAIRY TAIL.

21
00:01:11,583 --> 00:01:13,958
- ( theme music playing )
- ( singing in Japanese )

22
00:02:43,041 --> 00:02:44,875
- Natsu:
PREVIOUSLY ON "FAIRY TAIL."

23
00:02:44,958 --> 00:02:46,250
- WHY WON'T YOU 
GO LOOK FOR HIM?

24
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:48,125
- I'M NOT LEAVING
WITHOUT MACAO!

25
00:02:49,541 --> 00:02:50,958
- Macao:
I OWE YOU ONE, BUDDY.

26
00:02:51,041 --> 00:02:53,208
- NATSU AND GRAY,
I HAVE AN IMPORTANT FAVOR

27
00:02:53,291 --> 00:02:54,708
THAT I NEED TO
ASK OF YOU.

28
00:02:54,791 --> 00:02:56,041
- Natsu: HEY ERZA,
I'LL COME WITH YOU,

29
00:02:56,125 --> 00:02:57,541
BUT ONLY UNDER ONE CONDITION.

30
00:02:57,625 --> 00:02:59,500
I WANT A REMATCH WHEN WE
GET BACK TO FAIRY TAIL. 

31
00:02:59,583 --> 00:03:01,375
- I ACCEPT YOUR CHALLENGE.

32
00:03:01,458 --> 00:03:03,333
- Lucy: YOU'RE NOT REALLY
GONNA FIGHT, ARE YOU?

33
00:03:06,375 --> 00:03:08,791
- Doma: THE EISENWALD GUILD
MAY HAVE BEEN DEFEATED,

34
00:03:08,875 --> 00:03:10,958
BUT THAT IS ONLY ONE
SMALL VICTORY

35
00:03:11,041 --> 00:03:12,791
IN A MUCH LARGER BATTLE.

36
00:03:12,875 --> 00:03:14,375
- Michello: THE NUMBER OF
DARK GUILDS HAS BEEN GROWING

37
00:03:14,458 --> 00:03:16,125
AT QUITE AN ALARMING RATE.

38
00:03:16,208 --> 00:03:18,625
- WE HAVE TO COME UP WITH
A PLAN TO ELIMINATE THEM ALL.

39
00:03:18,708 --> 00:03:20,541
- Shitou:
BUT HOW WOULD WE DO THAT?

40
00:03:20,625 --> 00:03:22,958
- HOWEVER IT'S DONE,
WE CANNOT ALLOW ZEREF'S MAGIC

41
00:03:23,041 --> 00:03:24,833
TO FALL INTO
THE WRONG HANDS AGAIN.

42
00:03:24,916 --> 00:03:27,416
- I DON'T UNDERSTAND
HOW EISENWALD WAS ABLE

43
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:30,625
TO OBTAIN A TOOL OF FORBIDDEN
MAGIC IN THE FIRST PLACE.

44
00:03:30,708 --> 00:03:32,750
- I HATE TO SAY IT,
BUT THE BLAME MAY EXTEND

45
00:03:32,833 --> 00:03:34,416
ALL THE WAY TO
THE HIGHEST LEVELS.

46
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:36,041
- WHATEVER THE CASE,

47
00:03:36,125 --> 00:03:38,583
ALTHOUGH THEY'RE USUALLY
JUST A THORN IN OUR SIDES,

48
00:03:38,666 --> 00:03:41,750
IT SEEMS FAIRY TAIL PROVED
TO BE QUITE USEFUL.

49
00:03:41,833 --> 00:03:44,416
- THEY TOOK DOWN
AN ENTIRE GUILD 

50
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,958
WITH A HANDFUL OF WIZARDS.
THAT IS QUITE A FEAT.

51
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:48,291
- ( overlapping chatter ) 
- I STILL DON'T LIKE THEM.

52
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:49,833
- YOU MAY NOT
WANT TO ACCEPT IT,

53
00:03:49,916 --> 00:03:51,958
BUT THAT'S THE REALITY
OF THE SITUATION.

54
00:03:52,041 --> 00:03:55,666
IN THE END, THE ATTACK ON
THE GUILD MASTERS WAS PREVENTED,

55
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:57,416
LIVES WERE SPARED

56
00:03:57,500 --> 00:04:00,250
AND NONE OF US HAD TO GIVE UP
OUR HARD EARNED POSITIONS

57
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:02,791
ON THIS COUNCIL
TO SAVE FACE.

58
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:04,666
- YOU FOOL!
ARE YOU INSINUATING

59
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:06,541
THE COUNCIL IS
SOMEHOW TO BLAME?

60
00:04:06,625 --> 00:04:08,125
- ENOUGH OF THIS NONSENSE.

61
00:04:08,208 --> 00:04:10,625
FAIRY TAIL'S GOOD DEEDS
ARE OVERSHADOWED

62
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:12,625
BY THEIR RECKLESS DESTRUCTION.

63
00:04:12,708 --> 00:04:14,791
- THEN WHY DON'T WE
TAKE THE OPPORTUNITY

64
00:04:14,875 --> 00:04:17,416
TO DISCUSS THE MATTER
WITH THEM?

65
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:22,208
- ( Happy speaking )

66
00:04:23,625 --> 00:04:25,416
- ( bell ringing )

67
00:04:28,875 --> 00:04:30,750
- Lucy: "EISENWALD'S FAILED
ATTEMPT TO ATTACK

68
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:32,125
THE GUILD MASTERS WITH LULLABY

69
00:04:32,208 --> 00:04:33,708
ENDED UP BEING BIG NEWS.

70
00:04:33,791 --> 00:04:35,291
IT MADE ALL THE PAPERS,

71
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:37,708
AND IT SEEMED LIKE
EVERYBODY WAS TALKING ABOUT IT.

72
00:04:37,791 --> 00:04:40,875
BEFORE JOINING FAIRY TAIL, 
I NEVER WOULD HAVE IMAGINED

73
00:04:40,958 --> 00:04:43,041
I'D BE PART OF
SUCH A BIG EVENT.

74
00:04:43,125 --> 00:04:46,166
IT FEELS AWESOME, BUT I'M NOT
GONNA LET IT GO TO MY HEAD.

75
00:04:46,250 --> 00:04:48,500
IT STILL MAKES MY HEART
SKIP A BEAT

76
00:04:48,583 --> 00:04:50,666
WHEN I THINK ABOUT
EVERYTHING WE WENT THROUGH.

77
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:52,625
I HEARD THAT THE AUTHORITIES

78
00:04:52,708 --> 00:04:54,083
CAUGHT MOST OF THE
EISENWALD MEMBERS

79
00:04:54,166 --> 00:04:55,500
WHO WERE INVOLVED.

80
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:57,166
THEY EVEN GOT A HOLD
OF KAGEYAMA,

81
00:04:57,250 --> 00:04:59,500
SO THAT'S REASSURING AT LEAST.

82
00:04:59,583 --> 00:05:01,500
THE SCARY THING IS,

83
00:05:01,583 --> 00:05:04,083
THEY STILL HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO TRACK DOWN ERIGOR.

84
00:05:04,166 --> 00:05:08,083
I'M WORRIED HE MIGHT SHOW UP AT
FAIRY TAIL LOOKING FOR REVENGE.

85
00:05:08,166 --> 00:05:09,833
BUT I'LL BE OKAY,
'CAUSE I'M WITH THE GUILD'S

86
00:05:09,916 --> 00:05:11,500
STRONGEST TEAM.

87
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:14,166
ERZA, GRAY, AND NATSU
HAVE MY BACK NO MATTER WHAT.

88
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:15,708
NOT TO MENTION HAPPY.

89
00:05:15,791 --> 00:05:18,500
FAIRY TAIL IS AWESOME,
AND MY FELLOW MEMBERS 

90
00:05:18,583 --> 00:05:20,125
ARE REALLY GREAT PEOPLE.

91
00:05:20,208 --> 00:05:22,500
SO DON'T WORRY, MOM.
I'M DOING FINE.

92
00:05:22,583 --> 00:05:26,083
P.S. PLEASE DON'T TELL DAD
ANY OF THIS, 'KAY?"

93
00:05:26,166 --> 00:05:27,916
( sighs )

94
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,250
MAYBE I'LL DO A LITTLE
SHOPPING LATER TODAY. 

95
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:34,125
SAVING THE WORLD
FROM EVIL IS COOL AND ALL,

96
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:37,291
BUT SOMETIMES IT'S NICE
JUST TO RELAX AT HOME. 

97
00:05:37,375 --> 00:05:39,833
- MAN, 70,000 JEWEL
A MONTH IS DIRT CHEAP

98
00:05:39,916 --> 00:05:40,708
FOR A PLACE LIKE THIS.

99
00:05:40,791 --> 00:05:42,708
YOU TOTALLY SCORED, LUCY.

100
00:05:42,791 --> 00:05:44,208
- INTRUDER ALERT!

101
00:05:44,291 --> 00:05:45,958
( grunts )

102
00:05:46,041 --> 00:05:48,291
NO STRIPPING
IN MY HOUSE, BUDDY.

103
00:05:48,375 --> 00:05:50,916
- HEY, GIVE ME A MINUTE
TO EXPLAIN, WOULD YOU? 

104
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,291
I WAS NAKED
WHEN I GOT HERE.

105
00:05:53,375 --> 00:05:55,708
- GET OUT. - SO YOU FORGOT
ABOUT TODAY, HUH?

106
00:05:55,791 --> 00:05:58,125
I FIGURED YOU WOULDN'T REMEMBER,
SO I CAME BY TO REMIND YOU.

107
00:05:58,208 --> 00:05:59,541
- ABOUT WHAT?

108
00:05:59,625 --> 00:06:02,083
- WELL, LET ME TRY
AND JOG YOUR MEMORY.

109
00:06:02,166 --> 00:06:05,625
REMEMBER WHEN NATSU CHALLENGED
ERZA AT THE TRAIN STATION?

110
00:06:05,708 --> 00:06:07,833
- ( crowd cheering )
- FIGHT FIGHT FIGHT!

111
00:06:07,916 --> 00:06:09,958
- SHOW HIM WHO'S BOSS, ERZA!
- COME ON, NATSU!

112
00:06:11,666 --> 00:06:13,291
- Gray: THEY'RE ABOUT
TO FIGHT THEIR REMATCH.

113
00:06:13,375 --> 00:06:14,791
- ( laughing )
- ( gasps )

114
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:17,166
NO WAY!  THEY'RE REALLY
GOING THROUGH WITH IT? 

115
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:18,750
- OH, HEY, LUCY.

116
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:20,500
- WELL, IF THOSE TWO
VALUE THEIR MANHOOD,

117
00:06:20,583 --> 00:06:22,166
THEN THEY'D BETTER 
GO THROUGH WITH IT.

118
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:23,833
- ERZA'S NOT A MAN.

119
00:06:23,916 --> 00:06:25,458
- BUT YOU GOTTA ADMIT
SHE'S MANLY.

120
00:06:25,541 --> 00:06:27,375
- Lucy: AREN'T YOU WORRIED
THIS FIGHT COULD

121
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:29,000
TEAR OUR STRONGEST TEAM APART?

122
00:06:29,083 --> 00:06:31,750
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
OUR STRONGEST TEAM?

123
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:33,666
- YOU, NATSU, AND ERZA,
YOU DUMMY.

124
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:35,625
YOU'RE THE THREE STRONGEST
WIZARDS IN THE GUILD.

125
00:06:35,708 --> 00:06:37,750
- WE ARE?  YEAH, RIGHT.

126
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:39,708
WHAT IDIOT
FED YOU THAT LINE?

127
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:44,583
- ( crying )
- OH, YOU'RE NOT AN IDIOT, MIRA.

128
00:06:44,666 --> 00:06:47,250
- SMOOTH MOVE, GRAY. - I'LL
HAND IT TO NATSU AND GRAY.

129
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:49,083
THEY'RE TOUGH LITTLE DUDES.

130
00:06:49,166 --> 00:06:51,833
BUT NEITHER OF THEM ARE EVEN 
CLOSE TO BEING THE STRONGEST.

131
00:06:51,916 --> 00:06:54,208
THERE ARE GUYS IN FAIRY TAIL
WHO ARE STRONGER THAN

132
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:55,708
BOTH OF THEM COMBINED.

133
00:06:55,791 --> 00:06:57,291
LIKE THIS GUY.

134
00:06:57,375 --> 00:06:59,708
- BUT CALLING ERZA THE STRONGEST
WOMAN IN THE GUILD

135
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:01,291
IS A PRETTY SAFE BET.

136
00:07:01,375 --> 00:07:03,041
- AS FAR AS THE GUYS,
IT'S A TOUGH CALL,

137
00:07:03,125 --> 00:07:05,125
BUT I'D PUT MY MONEY 
ON LAXUS OR MYSTOGAN.

138
00:07:05,208 --> 00:07:07,625
- ALL I MEANT WAS THE THREE OF
THEM WORK WELL TOGETHER

139
00:07:07,708 --> 00:07:09,125
AND THEY HAVE THE BEST
TEAM CHEMISTRY

140
00:07:09,208 --> 00:07:10,708
IN ALL OF FAIRY TAIL.

141
00:07:10,791 --> 00:07:12,541
- OKAY.  AND THIS IS COMING
FROM THE SAME PERSON

142
00:07:12,625 --> 00:07:14,291
WHO SENT ME ON A MISSION
TO KEEP NATSU AND GRAY

143
00:07:14,375 --> 00:07:16,333
FROM KILLING EACH OTHER 
WHEN ERZA WASN'T AROUND?

144
00:07:16,416 --> 00:07:19,375
- GOTTA SAY, I'M PRETTY PSYCHED 
TO SEE HOW THIS FIGHT TURNS OUT.

145
00:07:19,458 --> 00:07:22,833
- OH YEAH? I'M SURE SHE'LL END
UP MOPPING THE FLOOR WITH HIM.

146
00:07:22,916 --> 00:07:25,708
- IT'S BEEN QUITE AWHILE SINCE
WE'VE SQUARED OFF LIKE THIS,

147
00:07:25,791 --> 00:07:27,333
HASN'T IT, NATSU?

148
00:07:27,416 --> 00:07:29,208
- I WAS JUST
A LITTLE KID BACK THEN.

149
00:07:29,291 --> 00:07:31,041
TODAY'S GONNA BE DIFFERENT.

150
00:07:31,125 --> 00:07:32,750
'CAUSE I'M TAKING YOU DOWN,
ERZA.

151
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,916
- WELL, I'M NOT GOING
TO GO EASY ON YOU.

152
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,250
IN FACT,
I HAVE THE PERFECT ARMOR

153
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:38,416
FOR THIS OCCASION.

154
00:07:56,291 --> 00:07:59,416
- THAT'S FLAME EMPRESS ARMOR.
GOOD CHOICE AGAINST FIRE MAGIC.

155
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:02,250
- SO NOW NATSU'S FLAMES
WILL ONLY BE HALF AS EFFECTIVE.

156
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:04,875
- COME ON, ERZA, AT LEAST GIVE
THE KID A FIGHTING CHANCE.

157
00:08:04,958 --> 00:08:07,125
- HMM.

158
00:08:07,208 --> 00:08:09,083
PUT ME DOWN FOR ERZA
IN THE FIRST ROUND. 

159
00:08:09,166 --> 00:08:11,666
- YOU'RE BETTING AGAINST
YOUR OWN BEST FRIEND?

160
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:13,416
WHY ARE YOU GUYS
PICKING SIDES?

161
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:15,083
I DON'T WANT
EITHER OF THEM TO LOSE.

162
00:08:15,166 --> 00:08:16,833
- GET INTO THE SPIRIT, LUCY.

163
00:08:16,916 --> 00:08:20,708
- WOW, FLAME EMPRESS ARMOR, HUH?
GOOD NEWS FOR ME.

164
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:23,958
THAT MEANS I CAN TURN UP
THE HEAT AS HIGH AS I WANT TO.

165
00:08:25,375 --> 00:08:26,875
- ROUND ONE, START!

166
00:08:26,958 --> 00:08:28,500
- ( grunts )

167
00:08:31,083 --> 00:08:33,000
( grunting )

168
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:38,875
( shouts )

169
00:08:38,958 --> 00:08:40,291
- ( cheering )

170
00:08:40,375 --> 00:08:41,833
( screaming )

171
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:47,041
- WHOA.
- SEE?  IT'S A GOOD FIGHT, HUH?

172
00:08:47,125 --> 00:08:48,583
- THIS FIGHT SUCKS.

173
00:08:50,625 --> 00:08:52,083
- ( groans )

174
00:08:58,166 --> 00:09:00,250
- THIS FIGHT IS OVER.

175
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:01,875
- ( crowd chattering )

176
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:04,166
- MAY I HAVE
YOUR ATTENTION PLEASE?

177
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:06,875
I HAVE COME HERE ON BEHALF
OF THE MAGIC COUNCIL.

178
00:09:06,958 --> 00:09:08,750
- NO WAY.
- SERIOUSLY?

179
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:10,416
- WHY WOULD THE COUNCIL
SEND HER HERE?

180
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,875
- AM I THE ONLY ONE
WHO NOTICED SHE'S A FROG?!

181
00:09:12,958 --> 00:09:15,333
- AS A RESULT OF
THE EISENWALD INCIDENT,

182
00:09:15,416 --> 00:09:17,500
A MEMBER OF YOUR GUILD
HAS BEEN CHARGED WITH 

183
00:09:17,583 --> 00:09:20,208
11 COUNTS OF CRIMINAL
PROPERTY DAMAGE.

184
00:09:20,291 --> 00:09:23,916
ERZA SCARLET,
YOU ARE UNDER ARREST.

185
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:27,083
- HUH?  YOU'RE PUTTING HER
UNDER A-- WHAT?!

186
00:09:27,166 --> 00:09:29,500
- AND THEN THIS HAPPENED.

187
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:36,625
- ( murmurs )

188
00:09:36,708 --> 00:09:39,583
- ( sighs )

189
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,125
- Natsu:
THIS ISN'T FAIR, YOU GUYS!

190
00:09:45,208 --> 00:09:46,625
LET ME OUT OF HERE ALREADY!

191
00:09:46,708 --> 00:09:48,833
- NATSU, TRY TO CALM DOWN.

192
00:09:48,916 --> 00:09:50,458
- LET ME OUT!
PRETTY PRETTY PLEASE?

193
00:09:50,541 --> 00:09:51,916
- YOU'LL GO ON A RAMPAGE.

194
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,250
- I'LL BE GOOD, I SWEAR.

195
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:54,458
NOW PLEASE JUST
TURN ME BACK

196
00:09:54,541 --> 00:09:55,708
TO THE WAY I WAS BEFORE.

197
00:09:55,791 --> 00:09:57,375
- THE SECOND WE TURN YOU BACK,

198
00:09:57,458 --> 00:09:58,875
YOU'LL RUN OUT
TO SAVE ERZA. 

199
00:09:58,958 --> 00:10:00,250
- GIVE ME A BREAK.
I COULDN'T CARE LESS

200
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:01,583
WHAT HAPPENS TO HER.

201
00:10:01,666 --> 00:10:03,250
- EVEN IF YOU WANTED
TO HELP HER,

202
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:05,375
IT'S NOT LIKE WE CAN
FACE OFF WITH THE COUNCIL.

203
00:10:05,458 --> 00:10:07,458
- BUT DON'T THOSE JERKS
ON THE COUNCIL REALIZE 

204
00:10:07,541 --> 00:10:08,875
THAT ERZA DID
WHAT SHE HAD TO DO

205
00:10:08,958 --> 00:10:10,458
TO SAVE THE LIVES
OF THE GUILD MASTERS

206
00:10:10,541 --> 00:10:12,541
FROM THOSE BAD GUYS
AND THEIR EVIL DEATH FLUTE?!

207
00:10:12,625 --> 00:10:14,375
- IF THE MAGIC COUNCIL
SAYS YOU'RE GUILTY,

208
00:10:14,458 --> 00:10:16,291
THEN YOU'RE GUILTY.
END OF STORY.

209
00:10:16,375 --> 00:10:18,458
THEY DON'T CARE
WHAT WE HAVE TO SAY.

210
00:10:18,541 --> 00:10:20,041
- I JUST DON'T GET IT.

211
00:10:20,125 --> 00:10:21,833
WE'VE DESTROYED PLENTY
STUFF IN THE PAST

212
00:10:21,916 --> 00:10:23,666
AND THEY NEVER MADE
A BIG DEAL OUT OF IT.

213
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:25,916
- I KNOW.
IT DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

214
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:29,875
- IT'S LIKE THERE'S
SOME OTHER REASON FOR THIS.

215
00:10:32,041 --> 00:10:34,916
- Narrator: THIS BUILDING
HOUSES THE FIORE BRANCH

216
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,000
OF THE MAGIC COUNCIL.

217
00:10:37,083 --> 00:10:40,500
AS WE SPEAK, ERZA SCARLET
IS BEING LED DOWN ITS HALLS,

218
00:10:40,583 --> 00:10:43,583
DRAWING CLOSER TO THE TRIAL
THAT AWAITS HER.

219
00:10:43,666 --> 00:10:46,166
- ( croaking )

220
00:10:53,083 --> 00:10:54,125
- ( chuckles )

221
